Citation.sTitle: Volumetric and viscosity properties of dicationic ionic liquids in (glucose + water) solutions at T = 298.15 K
Citation.sAbstract: Apparent molar volumes VU;DIL and viscosity B-coefficients of the dicationic ionic liquids (DILs) in {glucose (Glc) + water} solutions were determined from density and viscosity measurements at T = 298.15 K. Limiting apparent molar volumes V0 U;DIL of the DILs, volumetric interaction parameters, and activation energies Dl0 DIL were also obtained, together with the contributions of the solvent property B1 and the dicationic ionic liquid  solvent interaction B2 to the B-coefficient. A linear relation was observed between V0 U;DIL and the number of methylene groups n(CH2) in the alkyl linkage chain of DILs. Volumetric interaction parameters and B2 values are positive and increase with increasing the length of alkyl linkage chain of the dication. The DIL  glucose interactions were discussed in terms of the size and solvation of the DILs and glucose.
